transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi. My name is Robert Womble, and I need to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Hey, Mr. Womble, what's your date of birth so I can pull your account up?

Speaker 2: 5-6-1969.

Speaker 1: Thank you. And while I'm pulling up your account, may I ask the reason for wanting to cancel your prescription?

Speaker 2: I just found something I like better.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let's see here. It looks like you're getting our generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: It wasn't working for you?

Speaker 1: No, I just like the other one better.

Speaker 2: I tried some different ones, and I guess I like the Regiette better.

Speaker 1: Okay. Did you want to try our Viagra AGV? It's our newest Viagra.

Speaker 2: I thought that's what I was getting.

Speaker 1: No, it looks like you were getting the generic Viagra, the 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: It doesn't look like the AGV.

Speaker 1: I could send you a free sample of the AGV if you want to try that out.

Speaker 2: No, I'm good.

Speaker 1: Okay. I'm going to go ahead and cancel this for you,

Speaker 2: and then going forward you won't be receiving any more prescription refills.

Speaker 1: But I just got charged for a new dose, so that one's going to be still shipped to me, correct?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that one has already shipped. I already have a tracking number on it.

Speaker 1: It shows it's going to be delivered on the 17th.

Speaker 2: Okay. No worries.

Speaker 1: All right. So it's canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right. Bye-bye.
